# Direnv integration for Nix flake development
# Automatically loads the Nix development shell when entering this directory
#
# Installation:
#   1. Install direnv: https://direnv.net/
#   2. Hook direnv into your shell (~/.bashrc or ~/.zshrc):
#      eval "$(direnv hook bash)"  # for bash
#      eval "$(direnv hook zsh)"   # for zsh
#   3. Allow this directory:
#      direnv allow .
#
# Features:
#   - Automatic Python environment activation
#   - Docker and docker-compose in PATH
#   - Poetry and uv available
#   - Environment variables set

use flake

# Optional: Load local .env file if it exists
dotenv_if_exists .env

# Optional: Set custom environment variables
export INTEGRATION_TESTS_ENV="development"
export PYTHONUNBUFFERED=1
